text: Malcolm E Barnes is a male former swimmer who competed for England. ==Swimming career== He represented England in the 440 yards freestyle and freestyle relay at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. He was a member of the Stoke Newington Club. ==References== Category:English male swimmers Category:Swimmers at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Possibly living people Category:Year of birth missing
